NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|This hand also is a good illustration of why you should follow my competitive bidding guidelines. One of my important guidelines is, never let the opponents play at the 2 level when they have an 8+ card fit. On this hand, E/W make 4 diamonds. So letting us make 2 hearts is going to be a very bad result. Cheryl must bid 3 diamonds once Toots passes 2 hearts. Once in a while it will not work out, but more of the time, letting us play 2H will be a bad result for E/W.|
PG| ***** 116 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, if you are sure the opponents have an 8+ card fit, and have stopped in 2, make sure you do not let them play there.|
